{{ pc.standardSection('id="composition"') }}
  <h3 id="composition">Composition With Other Standards</h3>
  <ul style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
    <li><strong><a href="/projects/webnotifications/">Web Notifications</a></strong> &mdash; the
      non-fungible sibling: closed-app push delivery. The by-purpose split (<a href="/backlog/455-server-to-client-delivery-transport-home-by-purpose-vs-by-me/">#455</a>)
      keeps push and open-app realtime in distinct homes.</li>
    <li><strong>Render intents (Web Intents)</strong> &mdash; how live data is presented/announced
      (presence indicators, live-region updates) is a render concern composed on top, never owned by the
      transport.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/projects/webreliability/">Web Reliability</a></strong> &mdash; reconnect /
      backoff on a dropped connection is a recovery concern the reliability registry can own; the
      transport surfaces <code>close</code>/<code>error</code> for it to act on.</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/projects/webaudit/">Web Audit</a> / <a href="/projects/webreporting/">Web
      Reporting</a></strong> &mdash; connection lifecycle events are a report/audit source.</li>
  </ul>
{{ pc.endStandardSection() }}

{{ pc.standardSection('id="status"') }}
  <h3 id="status">Status</h3>
  <p>
    Web Realtime is in <strong>concept</strong> phase; the transport-negotiation protocol's contract is
    specified here. The home and the by-purpose transport split were ratified in
    <a href="/backlog/455-server-to-client-delivery-transport-home-by-purpose-vs-by-me/">#455</a> (Fork 2).
    Follow-ons: a native default <code>CustomTransportProvider</code> (SSE/WebSocket negotiation), the
    WebTransport capability probe, and presence/live-data render intents in Web Intents.
  </p>
  <h4 style="margin-top: 1rem;">Open Questions</h4>
  <ul style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
    <li>Does negotiation re-evaluate mid-session (a WebTransport upgrade once probed available), or is the
      channel fixed at <code>connect</code>?</li>
    <li>Is reconnect/backoff owned here or delegated wholesale to <a href="/projects/webreliability/">Web
      Reliability</a>'s recovery registry?</li>
    <li>Does the protocol standardize a message envelope (so channels are wire-compatible) or stay
      payload-opaque like the push <code>DeliveryReceipt</code>?</li>
  </ul>
{{ pc.endStandardSection() }}
